.TH WORKCELL 1 "2026-03-22" "Workcell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
workcell \- bounded runtime launcher for coding agents
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B workcell
[\fIoptions\fR] [\fB--\fR \fIprovider-args\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B workcell
starts the selected coding agent inside a bounded local runtime with explicit
isolation and policy controls.
.B workcell
launches the selected provider directly inside that runtime; there is no
separate attach or connect step after launch.
The Tier 1 path is a dedicated Colima virtual machine profile on macOS plus a
hardened container inside that VM.
The managed runtime mounts
.I /tmp
as
.B noexec
and uses
.I /state/tmp
as the exec-capable temporary directory via
.BR TMPDIR .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --agent codex|claude|gemini
Select the provider to run. This option is required.
.TP
.B --agent-autonomy yolo|prompt
Select the provider approval posture. The default is
.BR yolo ,
which means Workcell injects the provider's no-prompt mode. Use
.BR prompt
to opt back into the provider's normal approval flow.
Prompt autonomy is a lower-assurance choice because provider-native approval
state or session-local policy can change during the live session.
.TP
.B --agent-arg VALUE
Append provider-native argv at launch. This option is repeatable and does not
require repeating
.BR codex ,
.BR claude ,
or
.BR gemini
in the provider argv. These values are still validated as ordinary user-supplied
provider arguments inside the managed runtime.
.TP
.B --container-mutability ephemeral|readonly
Select whether the inner runtime root filesystem is writable but session-local
.RB ( ephemeral )
or read-only
.RB ( readonly ).
The default is
.BR ephemeral .
When
.B ephemeral
is selected, Workcell also allows
.BR apt
and
.BR apt-get
to reach the pinned Debian snapshot endpoints so transient build tooling can be
installed without widening to arbitrary distro mirrors.
Successful package mutations are treated as a lower-assurance in-session
downgrade because maintainer scripts run as root inside the mutable container;
Workcell warns when that happens and keeps the downgrade visible until the
container exits.
.TP
.B --container-cpu COUNT
Set an explicit CPU limit for the inner runtime container.
.TP
.B --container-memory SIZE
Set an explicit memory limit for the inner runtime container, for example
.BR 4g .
.TP
.B --injection-policy PATH
Use an explicit host-side injection policy for this launch. Workcell mounts
credential sources read-only from their original host paths and stages the
selected docs, copied files, and SSH material into per-session runtime state
instead of passing through host homes or sockets directly.
.TP
.B --no-default-injection-policy
Ignore
.I ~/.config/workcell/injection-policy.toml
for this launch even if it exists.
.TP
.B --ui cli|gui
Select the surface to launch. Only
.BR cli
is currently implemented as a preserved-boundary path.
.TP
.B --mode strict|build|breakglass
Select the runtime profile. The default is
.BR strict .
.TP
.B --prepare
Seed or refresh the reviewed runtime image before continuing with the requested
launch. This is the recommended first-run path.
.TP
.B --repair-profile
Delete a conflicting unmanaged Colima profile before launch so Workcell can
recreate it with reviewed mounts and policy. On
.BR strict ,
this also implies
.B --prepare
because the recreated profile starts empty.
.TP
.B --ack-breakglass
Required with
.B --mode breakglass
to make the higher-trust path explicit.
.TP
.B --ack-arbitrary-command
Required with
.B --allow-arbitrary-command
to make lower-assurance boundary-debugging command passthrough explicit.
.TP
.B --workspace PATH
Select the workspace to mount inside the runtime. The default is the current
directory.
.TP
.B --allow-nongit-workspace
Allow a non-git workspace that contains an explicit agent marker file.
.TP
.B --allow-arbitrary-command
Launch the runtime image with a direct container entrypoint after
.BR -- .
This is intended only for lower-assurance boundary debugging and is recorded in
the host audit log as a downgraded path.
.TP
.B --colima-profile NAME
Override the derived Colima profile name.
.TP
.B --vm-cpu COUNT
Set an explicit CPU count for the dedicated Colima VM.
.TP
.B --vm-memory GIB
Set an explicit memory size in GiB for the dedicated Colima VM.
.TP
.B --vm-disk GIB
Set an explicit disk size in GiB for the dedicated Colima VM.
.TP
.B --rebuild
Rebuild the runtime image before launch.
This is rejected on
.BR strict
unless
.B --prepare
is also set.
.TP
.B --dry-run
Print the selected runtime command and exit.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show usage information.
.SH PROFILES
.TP
.B strict
Allowlisted network access only, no host credential or control socket
passthrough, and provider-native bounded or constrained mode only where the
selected provider actually offers one. On this profile, direct native ELF
execution from mutable
.I /workspace
and
.I /state
paths is blocked, and mutable shebang scripts cannot target protected real
runtimes directly.
This profile requires a prebuilt reviewed runtime image and does not perform
cold builds or rebuilds unless
.B --prepare
explicitly tells Workcell to seed the image before continuing.
.TP
.B build
The same mount and secret restrictions as
.BR strict ,
with broader network access for dependency and build traffic.
Reviewed runtime-image creation and rebuilds happen here.
.TP
.B breakglass
Still inside the Workcell VM plus container boundary, but with unrestricted
network access. The managed entrypoint does not auto-inject unsafe provider
flags; any adapter-specific high-trust launch is a lower-assurance direct
provider path. This profile requires
.BR --ack-breakglass .
.SH NODE SURFACE
The public
.B node
surface exposed by the managed runtime is intended for workspace JavaScript, not
for launching provider entrypoints, repackaged workspace copies of the shipped
provider package trees, or loading native addons. Workcell blocks those paths
on the safe profiles so public
.B node
execution cannot retake unmediated native code execution.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/bin/workcell
Installed launcher path used by
.BR scripts/install.sh .
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/man/man1/workcell.1
Installed man page path used by
.BR scripts/install.sh .
.TP
.I ~/.config/workcell/injection-policy.toml
Default optional host-side injection policy. If present, Workcell mounts
credential sources read-only from their original host paths and stages the rest
of its contents into per-session runtime state unless
.B --no-default-injection-policy
is set.
.TP
.I ~/.colima/PROFILE/workcell.audit.log
Durable host-side audit log written by the managed launcher for real runs.
.SH SESSION INJECTIONS
The safe path does not allow ambient host passthrough for secrets, SSH agents,
or provider state. The supported way to place consistent material into every
session is a host-side injection policy.
.PP
Workcell treats injected content as three classes:
.IP \(bu 2
Non-secret common or provider-specific instructions rendered into provider home
docs such as
.BR AGENTS.md ,
.BR CLAUDE.md ,
and
.BR GEMINI.md .
.IP \(bu 2
Provider-native credentials mounted read-only from their original host paths
and copied into the ephemeral session home.
.IP \(bu 2
Copied files or directories staged into
.I /state/injected
or a non-reserved path under the ephemeral session home.
.IP \(bu 2
SSH material copied into the ephemeral in-container
.I ~/.ssh
with strict permissions.
.PP
The immutable adapter baselines under
.I adapters/
are never mutated in place. Repo-local
.BR AGENTS.md ,
.BR CLAUDE.md ,
and
.BR GEMINI.md
are masked inside the workspace and imported into the provider home docs
instead. On the default
.B --agent-autonomy yolo
path, managed provider policy such as Codex
.I rules/default.rules
stays read-only inside the session. On the explicit lower-assurance
.B --agent-autonomy prompt
path, Workcell seeds a session-local writable copy of the Codex rules tree so
provider-approved session amendments can persist across nested Codex launches
until the container exits.
Reusable provider and GitHub auth should go through
.BR [credentials]
in the injection policy rather than generic copied files.
.SH FIRST RUN AND RECOVERY
Recommended first launch:
.IP
.EX
workcell --prepare --agent codex --workspace /path/to/repo
.EE
.PP
Replace
.B codex
with
.B claude
or
.B gemini
for the corresponding provider.
.PP
Normal launch after the reviewed image already exists:
.IP
.EX
workcell --agent codex --workspace /path/to/repo
.EE
.PP
Prompted launch for a selected provider:
.IP
.EX
workcell --agent claude --agent-autonomy prompt --workspace /path/to/repo
.EE
.PP
Passing provider flags without repeating the provider command:
.IP
.EX
workcell --agent gemini --agent-arg --version --workspace /path/to/repo
.EE
.PP
Using an explicit injection policy:
.IP
.EX
workcell --prepare --agent codex --workspace /path/to/repo \\
  --injection-policy ~/.config/workcell/injection-policy.toml
.EE
.PP
If Workcell reports an unmanaged Colima profile, rerun with:
.IP
.EX
workcell --repair-profile --agent codex --workspace /path/to/repo
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
The command exits non-zero on validation failures, unsupported modes, missing
dependencies, or runtime launch errors.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR colima (1),
.BR docker (1)
